e consumer electronics original equipment manufacturers oems use sapphire faceplates for smartphones for the led market it sells  to inch material in core form and four six and eightinch material in polished and pss wafer form its principal customers are semiconductor device manufacturers and wafer polishing companies more from reuters » officers and directors don n aquilano independent chairman of the board age  bio  compensation   reuters timothy e brog president chief executive officer director age  bio  compensation   reuters mardel a graffy chief financial officer treasurer secretary age  bio  compensation   reuters christine richardson phd chief technology officer bio  compensation   reuters donald r caldwell cpa independent director age  bio  compensation   reuters michael e mikolajczyk independent director age  bio  compensation   reuters raymond j spencer independent director age  bio  compensation   reuters susan m westphal independent director bio  compensation   reuters full list on reuters » google finance beta available in hong kong  canada  us  china  ukinformation is provided as is and solely for informational purposes not for trading purposes or advice and may be delayedto see all exchange delays please see disclaimer google  google home  blog  help  report a problem  privacy policy  terms of service rubicon technology inc rbcnph company profile  reuterscom x edition united states africa américa latina عربي argentina brasil canada  deutschland españa france india italia  méxico россия united kingdom united states profile rubicon technology inc rbcnph related topics stocksstock screenertechnologysemiconductors overview news key developments people charts financials analysts research pulse rbcnph on philadelphia stock exchange usd  jun  change  chg   prev close  open  days high  days low  volume  avg vol  wk high  wk low  full description rubicon technology inc incorporated on february   is a vertically integrated electronic materials provider specializing in monocrystalline sapphire for applications in lightemitting diodes leds optical systems and specialty electronic devices the companys product lines include sapphire cores four and sixinch sapphire wafers four six and eightinch patterned sapphire substrate pss wafers and optical sapphire components the companys sapphire is also used as an exterior component in mobile devices specifically camera lens covers dual flashes and home buttons on certain newer model smartphones and as the crystal covering the faces of certain smart watches in addition some consumer electronics original equipment manufacturers oems use sapphire faceplates for smartphones for the led market it sells  to inch material in core form and four six and eightinch material in polished and pss wafer form its principal customers are semiconductor device manufacturers and wafer polishing companiesthe company rubicon has developed technology for every stage of production from raw material processing through crystal growth fabrication wafer finishing patterning and cleaning its crystal growth technique is referred to as es which produces sapphire crystals for use in its sapphire products es is derived from the kyropoulos method of crystal growth it markets and sells products through its direct sales force to customers in asia australia north america and europecorethe core product line consists of its sapphire cores drilled from sapphire boules with highprecision the sapphire cores are of  to  inches in diameter which its customers further process into wafers for use in led applications and into components such as lens covers for mobile devicespolishedthe polished product line consists of polished ultraclean four six and eightinch sapphire wafers its polished wafers undergo two polishing phases including both a mechanical and a chemical mechanical planarization phase its four and sixinch sapphire wafers are used as substrates for the manufacture of led chips and for other semiconductor applications such as silicononsapphire sos radio frequency integrated circuits rficspatterned sapphire substratesthe pss product line consists of polished ultraclean four and sixinch patterned sapphire wafers it offers customizable submicron patterning capability with dimensional tolerances within  of a micron it also offers smallest edge exclusion zone maximizing the usable wafer surface area yielding more chips per wafer its four six and eightinch pss wafers which are polished wafers that undergo additional processes of photolithography and dry plasma etching to produce a patterned surfaceopticalthe company offers optically polished windows and ground window blanks of sapphire it provides sapphire and other crystal products in various sizes shapes and product formats for specialty applications its optical sapphire components are available in various shapes and sizes including round and rectangular windows and blanks domes tubes and rods these optical sapphire products are used in equipment for a range of end markets including defense and aerospace medical devices oil and gas drilling semiconductor manufacturing and other markets » full overview of rbcnph company address rubicon technology inc  e green stbensenville   il    p f  company web links home page officers  directors name compensation don aquilano  timothy brog  mardel graffy  christine richardson  donald caldwell  » more officers  directors rubicon technology inc news briefaldebaran capital reports  percent stake in rubicon technology jun   briefrubicon technology announces reverse stock split may   briefrubicon technology names timothy brog as ceo mar   » more rbcnph news related topics stocksstock screenertechnologysemiconductors rubicon technology inc  photonics buyers guide menu photonics media buyers guide edu photonics register login prodspec products companies industries white papers handbook media manage listing buy print edition advertise search this week in photonicslight matters monthly alertphotonics spect